    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Trim your green stalk[s]<strong> </strong>off the<strong> aubergine[s]</strong> and chop in half widthways, then cut lengthways into strips</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour </strong>and<strong> aubergine strips </strong>to a bowl and mix well so the aubergine is evenly coated</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chicken-thigh-and-aubergine-stir-fry-with-pea-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated</strong> <strong>aubergine strips</strong> (save any excess cornflour in the bowl for later) and cook for 7-8 min or until starting to brown all over</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chicken-thigh-and-aubergine-stir-fry-with-pea-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chicken-thigh-and-aubergine-stir-fry-with-pea-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced chicken </strong>to the bowl with the <strong>remaining cornflour </strong>and mix well until evenly coated</p><p>Once the aubergine has browned, increase the heat to high, then add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>and cook for a further 10-12 min or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chicken-thigh-and-aubergine-stir-fry-with-pea-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>in a bowl with the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and<strong> rice vinegar</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> to the bowl and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> stir-fry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chicken-thigh-and-aubergine-stir-fry-with-pea-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked through, add the <strong>stir-fry sauce</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until sticky \u2013 this is your <strong>sticky chicken & aubergine stir-fry</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chicken-thigh-and-aubergine-stir-fry-with-pea-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p><p>Mix the <strong>refreshed peas </strong>through the <strong>cooked rice </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> pea rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chicken-thigh-and-aubergine-stir-fry-with-pea-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sticky chicken & aubergine stir-fry</strong> with the <strong>pea rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
